body:
The complaint is not that `LayerNormalization_token_12` is not in the ONNX standard. The problem seems to be with the LayerNorm CUDA kernel implementation (`CUDA error cudaErrorInvalidConfiguration:invalid configuration argument`).

When you set optimization level to ORT_DISABLE_ALL, the LayerNorm fusion doesn't kick-in and it doesn't run the problematic CUDA kernel.

Can you provide a minimalistic model to repro ? @wangyems @tianleiwu : Can you please take a look at this potential issue with the LayerNorm CUDA kernel when you get a chance ?
Thanks. Yes that seems to be the issue. Will create a small model to show this issue.

This sounds strange. [LayerNormalization exists in ORT](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/229c9a4e1c2508fcac0dbe38418db1c9e9012833/onnxruntime/contrib_ops/cuda/cuda_contrib_kernels.cc#L72) as an contributed operator, so it should be runnable. Could you please share how do you install onnxruntime? Maybe there are some hard-coded constants such as number of GPU blocks causing this problem.
Found similar issue with an internal model. Will work on investigation.

issue.body:
**Description**: Describe your changes.
Previously, if input 'X' of LayerNorm has no data, we see CUDA error: cudaErrorInvalidConfiguration : invalid configuration argument. 
This change catches it earlier and provide better information for debugging.
